able enjoyment stemming from many life formsWith a renewed welcome for pleasure, the book also upholds a disruptive ethic. Ultimately, an immoderate God of love whose passionate enjoyment stems from the sufferings as well as joys of the cosmos offers another paradigm of lovingly enjoying oneself in relationship with passionate becomings that belong to many others.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aGod (Christianity). 0aPleasurexReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / General.2bisacsh  aMysticism.  acosmos.  aenjoyment.  afiesta.  aimmodesty.  aincarnation.  alove.  apassion.  apoetry.  aprocess.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311072903040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823263592zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823263592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823263592/original  a978-3-11-072903-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK